init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So they elect a diplomat to go meet with the leaders of the other nations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: For instance, the United States has successfully built a ship capable of traveling at 1/3 the speed of light.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world's leaders are not happy with the United States' progress.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The people of the United States are tired of war and want to live in peace.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are willing to share the tech but they want no part of war.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world leaders agree to these terms.
